wood Bowl]]\n| Concert Production\n|\n|-\n| 2017\n| rowspan=4| ''[[Waitress (musical)|Waitress]]''\n| rowspan=4| Jenna Hunterson\n| March 31 \u2013 June 11, 2017\n| rowspan=3| [[Brooks Atkinson Theatre]]\n| rowspan=3| [[Broadway theatre|Broadway]]\n| {{center|<ref>{{cite web |first=Lindsay |last= Kimble |title='Sugar, Butter, Broadway': Sara Bareilles Taking Over the Lead Role in Her Musical Waitress |url=https://people.com/theater/sara-bareilles-starring-in-waitress-broadway/ |date=February 16, 2017 |work=People}}</ref>}}\n|-\n| 2018\n| January 16 \u2013 March 11, 2018\n| {{center|<ref>{{cite web |first=Allison |last= Stubblebine |title=Sara Bareilles Returning to 'Waitress,' Joining Jason Mraz For Two Week Run |url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/broadway/8053916/sara-bareilles-waitress-jason-mraz-two-week-run-january-2018 |date=November 29, 2017 |website=Billboard }}</ref>}}\n|-\n| 2019\n| January 7 \u2013 February 3, 2019\n| {{center|<ref>{{cite web |first=Andrew |last= Gans |title=Sara Bareilles Will Return to Broadway's Waitress Opposite Tony Winner Gavin Creel |url=http://www.playbill.com/article/sara-bareilles-will-return-to-broadways-waitress-opposite-tony-winner-gavin-creel |date=December 7, 2018 |website=Playbill }}</ref>}}\n|-\n|-\n| 2020\n| January 27 \u2013 March 14, 2020\n| [[Adelphi Theatre]]\n| [[West End theatre|West End]]\n| {{center|<ref>{{cite web |first=Dan |last=Meyer |title=Sara Bareilles to Join Waitress in the West End Opposite Gavin Creel |url=http://www.playbill.com/article/sara-bareilles-to-join-waitress-in-the-west-end-opposite-gavin-creel |date=November 4, 2019 |website=Playbill }}</ref>}}\n|}\n\n==Awards and nominations==\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"width:100%\" \n|-\n! Year\n! Association\n! Category\n! Nominated work\n! Result\n! {{Abbr|Ref.|Reference(s)}}\n|-\n|2008\n|[https://www.ascap.com/press/2008/0312_sara_bareilles.aspx ASCAP Pop Music Awards]\n|ASCAP Vanguard Award\n|Herself\n|{{won}}\n|{{center|<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.ascap.com/press/2008/0312_sara_bareilles.aspx|title=SARA BAREILLES TO RECEIVE ASCAP VANGUARD AWARD AT 25TH ANNUAL ASCAP POP MUSIC AWARDS|work=www.ascap.com|access-date=March 27, 2018}}</ref>}}\n|-\n|rowspan=\"2\"| 2009\n|rowspan=\"3\"|[[Grammy Awards]]\n| [[Grammy Award for Song of the Year|Song of the Year]]\n|rowspan=\"2\"| \"[[Love Song (Sara Bareilles song)|Love Song]]\"\n| {{nom}}\n| {{center|<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.mtv.com/news/articles/1604545/20090208/story.jhtml |title=Grammy 2009 Winners List |date=February 8, 2009 |publisher=MTV }}</ref>}}\n|-\n|rowspan=\"2\"| [[Grammy Award for Best Female Pop Vocal Performance|Best Female Pop Vocal Performance]]\n| {{nom}}\n| {{center|<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.rockonthenet.com/grammy/popfemale.htm |title=Grammy Awards: Best Pop Vocal Performance \u2013 Female |publisher=Rock on the Net}}</ref>}}\n|-\n| rowspan=2|2011\n| \"[[King of Anything]]\"\n| {{nom}}\n| {{center|<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.grammy.com/nominees?year=2010&genre=24 |title=Nominees And Winners: Best Female Pop Vocal Performance |publisher=GRAMMY.com }}</ref>}}\n|-\n| [[Nielsen Broadcast Data Systems|BDSCertified Spin Awards]]\n| 700,000 Spins\n| \"[[Love Song (Sara Bareilles song)|Love Song]]\"\n| {{won}}\n|\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\" | 2012\n| rowspan=\"2\" | MVPA Awards\n| Best Directional Debut\n| rowspan=\"2\" | \"[[Gonna Get Over You]]\"\n| {{nom}}\n|\n|-\n| Best Choreography\n| {{won}}\n|\n|-\n| rowspan=6|2014\n| [[2014 World Music Awards|World Music Awards]]\n| World's Best Song\n| rowspan=\"4\" | \"[[Brave (Sara Bareilles song)|Brave]]\"\n| {{nom}}\n|\n|-\n| [[2014 iHeartRadio Music Awards|iHeartRadio Music Awards]]\n| Song of the Year\n| {{nom}}\n|<ref>[[2014 iHeartRadio Music Awards]]</ref>{{Circular reference|date=August 2019}}\n|-\n| [[2014 MTV Video Music Awards Japan|MTV Video Music Awards Japan]]\n| Best Choreography\n| {{nom}}\n|\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\" | [[56th Annual Grammy Awards|Grammy Awards]]\n| [[